<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="sec-lab-ultrasonic-navigation" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Lab: Using ultrasonics for navigation</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>In this lab we'll ultrasonics sensors to detect obstacles..</p>
  </introduction>
  <subsection xml:id="subsec-ultrasonic-sensors">
    <title>Ultrasonic sensors</title>
    <p>
      Follow along with the <url href="https://learn.parallax.com/courses/cyberbot-roaming-with-the-ping/">Roaming with the Ping</url> tutorial.
    </p>
    <p>
      The first objective is to show up the bot in action at the end of the tutorial.
    </p>
    <exercise label="ex-ultrasonic-with-tracking">
      <statement>
        <p>Combine the ultrasonic navigation code with your location-tracking code. You will likely need to modify how movement happens with the ping, to bring it closer to your tracking setup.</p>
        <p>After one minute of roaming free, the bot should enter a "head home" mode where it uses the location tracking to find its way to where it started (while reasonably avoiding obstacles by going around them).</p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>
    <p>This is the second objective for this lab.</p>
    <exercise label="ex-ultrasonic-with-tracking-and-remote-control">
      <statement>
        <p>Building on the previous objective, incorporate remote-control as follows:
          <ul>
            <li>The left-right buttons can be used to directly instruct the bot to turn.</li>
            <li>There is a button that can trigger the "return to home" behavior early.</li>
            <li>There is a button that can pause/unpause the bot's movement.</li>
          </ul>
        </p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>
    <p>This is the third and last objective for this lab.</p>
  </subsection>
</section>
